The paper deals with object classification in computer vision, specifically in the context of large-scale urban reconstruction. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of supervised learning and empirical study further supports this. The paper also deals with the problem of multi-label classification, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The application of the proposed approach to large-scale urban reconstruction suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
